DPRK Holidays to Be Commemorated in Ethiopia 
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Pyongyang, January 25 (KCNA) -- The Ethiopian preparatory committee was inaugurated with due ceremony in Addis Ababa on Jan. 17 to commemorate the Day of the Sun and February 16.
 At the ceremony Tatek Kassa, chairman of the Addis Ababa Youth Association of Ethiopia, was elected chairman of the preparatory committee and Nigatu Dagnachew Cherinet, vice-chairman of the association, vice-chairman of the preparatory committee and the general secretary of the association, secretary general of the preparatory committee. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The chairman of the preparatory committee said at the ceremony that it is great honor and joy for the youth and people of Ethiopia to form the preparatory committee on the occasion of the birthdays of President Kim Il Sung and leader Kim Jong Il. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 He referred to the immortal feats performed by the President and Kim Jong Il in the history of the youth movement by setting out the idea and policy of giving importance to the youth and successfully applying them. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Thanks to the outstanding Songun politics of Kim Jong Il, the Korean youth movement will grow stronger and develop, he stressed.
 It was decided at the ceremony to hold events throughout the country on those occasions.

E-Library and Gymnasium of Kim Chaek University of Technology Inaugurated 
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Pyongyang, January 25 (KCNA) -- An inaugural ceremony of e-library and gymnasium of Kim Chaek University of Technology took place on January 24. 
 The e-library with a total floor space of over 16,000 square metres is capable of accommodating more than 2,000 persons. All services ranging from the search of book catalogs to book and information reading and lecture are computerized.  The more than 4,000-seater gymnasium is capable of hosting various sporting events and trainings, art performances and meetings. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Leader Kim Jong Il during his visit to the university on January 4 expressed his great satisfaction over the successful construction of this modern e-library representing the appearance of an ideal society desired by the Korean people and the large multi-purpose gymnasium, and clearly indicated the orientation and ways of developing the e-library as the world's leading library under a plan and successfully managing and operating the gymnasium. 
 Present at the inaugural ceremony were Pak Pong Ju, premier of the Cabinet, Choe Thae Bok, secretary of the Central Committee of the Workers' Party of Korea, Kim Yong Jin, minister of Education, Ryang Man Gil, chairman of the Pyongyang City People's Committee, officials concerned, teachers and students of the university, servicepersons, builders and volunteers. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Addressing the ceremony, Pak Pong Ju recalled that while giving on-the-spot guidance to the university on September 19, Juche 90 (2001) Kim Jong Il clearly indicated the way for the university to follow in the new century, proposed the task for building a modern e-library and gymnasium and wisely led the whole course of their construction though he was very busy steering the Songun revolution. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The speaker underlined the need for all the officials and other working people to eternally hold President Kim Il Sung in high esteem as the sun of Juche, devotedly defend Kim Jong Il and remain true to the WPK's Songun idea and leadership.

Joint New Year Editorial Favored in Different Countries 
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Pyongyang, January 25 (KCNA) -- The Peruvian Communist Party and the Peruvian Association for the Study of Revolutionary Activities of Comrade Kim Jong Suk separately issued statements on Jan. 10 supporting the joint New Year editorial carried by the newspapers of the Workers' Party of Korea, the Korean People's Army and the Kim Il Sung Socialist Youth League.
 The Peruvian Communist Party in a statement said that the joint editorial powerfully encourages the party to support the struggle of the Korean people with firmer conviction of their cause. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The tasks for achieving the reunification of Korea set forth in the joint editorial are fully supported by the world progressives desirous of independence and Korea's reunification as they clarify the strategy and ways for realizing the reunification by the concerted efforts of the Korean people under the banner of the June 15 joint declaration, the statement stressed. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The above-said association in a statement noted that the Korean people smashed all sorts of anti-DPRK moves of the imperialists and worked world-startling miracles under the wise Songun leadership of Kim Jong Il last year, adding that the victory won by the Korean people vividly shows how outstanding and great the Songun politics enforced by him is. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 In the meantime, Siham Ahmad, chairman of the Egypt-Korea Friendship Association, and Subash Kaji Shrestha, chairman of the Study Forum for Self-Reliance of Nepal, separately issued statements in support of the joint editorial.

11th Sports Contest of Officials of National Institutions Opens 
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Pyongyang, January 25 (KCNA) -- The 11th sports contest of officials of national institutions for Paektusan Cup was opened.
 This is an annual event that takes place on the occasion of the auspicious February holiday. The contest provides officials of the ministries and national institutions with an opportunity to fully display their sports technique cultivated everyday and strikingly demonstrate the validity and the vitality of the Workers' Party of Korea's policy of putting sporting activities on a popular basis. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Its participants will compete in at least ten sports events including basketball, table-tennis, volleyball and sports for national defence at the Kim Il Sung Stadium and gymnasiums in Chongchun Street. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 An opening ceremony took place at the Basketball Gymnasium in Chongchun Street on Jan. 24. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Present there were Kim Jung Rin, secretary of the C.C., the WPK, and Ryom Sun Gil, chairman of the C.C., the General Federation of Trade Unions of Korea, and others. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The ceremony was followed by basketball and tug-of-war games.

16th Individual Contest for "Feb. 16 Art Prize" Opens 
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Pyongyang, January 25 (KCNA) -- The 16th individual contest for "February 16 Art Prize" opened.
 The contests held on the occasion of the auspicious February holiday since the first one proved to be a dynamic and vital performing art stage as it recorded a memorable page in the history of the Juche arts and deeply impressed the Korean artistes and audiences. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The Korean artistes are bringing their talents into full bloom under the wise leadership and loving care of Kim Jong Il who loves music and attaches importance to the arts. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The current contest drew 155 artistes who proved successful at the first and second phases of the contest held last year. It will be divided into panels of folk songs, national fillip musical instruments, national woodwind musical instruments, violin, cello, accordion and bayan. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The contest will be held at the State Drama Theatre and the Yun I Sang Concert Hall. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 An opening ceremony was held at the theatre on Jan. 24. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 All the participants in the contest will fully display their talents cultivated through their day-to-day practice and contribute to adding festivity to the February holiday.

Reception Given for Russian Diplomats 
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Pyongyang, January 25 (KCNA) -- The DPRK Foreign Ministry hosted a reception in honor of the staff members of the Russian embassy here Tuesday evening on the occasion of the New Year, Juche 95 (2006).
 Foreign Minister Paek Nam Sun in a speech said that the relations between the DPRK and Russia favorably developed in different fields last year under the deep care of the top leaders of the two countries. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 High-level delegations of Russia visited the DPRK on the occasions of the 60th anniversaries of the Workers' Party of Korea and the liberation of Korea and Russian art groups gave performances in Pyongyang and different local areas, he noted, and went on: &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Leader Kim Jong Il received the former presidential envoy to the Far East Region of the Russian Federation and his party and many other Russian guests and artistes who visited the DPRK last year and showed profound care for the development of the DPRK-Russia relations of friendship.
 President V. V. Putin's conferment of the Russian Medal Commemorating the 60th Anniversary of the Victory in the Great Patriotic War upon Kim Jong Il was an expression of high respect and deep friendship of the Russian people towards him. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Paek Nam Sun sincerely wished the Russian people greater success in their work to build powerful Russia under the leadership of Putin.
 Russian Ambassador Andrei Karlov said in a speech that 2005 was a significant year in the relations between the two countries.
 He noted that the Russian people are following with great interest the achievements made by the Korean people in building a great prosperous powerful nation, raising the international prestige of the country and improving the standard of people's living under the leadership of  Kim Jong Il.
 The celebrations of the 60th anniversary of the WPK offered us an opportunity to clearly realize how close the servicepersons and people of the DPRK are united around Kim Jong Il, he said, and continued: &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The Russian and Korean peoples jointly commemorated the 60th anniversary of the liberation of Korea and the defeat of Japanese militarism, and the relations between the two countries are based on militant friendship. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The Russia-DPRK relations will grow stronger and develop on a high level this year, too, on the basis of the agreements signed during the Pyongyang and Moscow meetings of Putin and Kim Jong Il and the treaty of friendship, good neighborliness and cooperation.

KCNA Urges U.S. to Remove Obstacle to Six-Party Talks 
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Pyongyang, January 25 (KCNA) -- A string of outcries are now being heard from Washington making the public skeptical about the attitude of the U.S. administration towards the six-party talks.
 Schneider, chairman of the Defence Science Committee in the U.S. Department of Defense, was reported to have uttered recently that it is illusion to judge that north Korea stands for the settlement of the nuclear issue and that additional sanctions are one of the options, asserting that north Korea is not likely to abandon its nuclear program through dialogue. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Such remarks are nothing but an expression of a deliberate intention of the hard-line conservatives to throw bigger obstacles to the six-party talks for the settlement of the nuclear issue. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The goal of the six-party talks is to denuclearize the Korean Peninsula. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 In order to make the talks serve the purpose of denuclearizing the peninsula it is necessary for the DPRK and the U.S. to find a practical way of solving the nuclear issue and trust and respect each other. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The U.S. "sanctions" against the DPRK are a wanton violation of the spirit of the joint statement adopted at the talks which calls for mutual respect and peaceful co-existence as they are intended to bring down the latter's system by stifling it. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Whoever has elementary political sense can know well that "sanctions" are an issue directly related to the six-party talks. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
  What matters is that the U.S. grossly twisted the DPRK's stand to realize the denuclearization of the Korean Peninsula and resume the six-party talks, not content with trumpeting that financial sanctions against Pyongyang have nothing to do with the talks and its stance on these sanctions is nothing but a pretext to delay the talks. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The denuclearization of the peninsula is the final goal of the DPRK and the cherished desire of the Korean nation. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The DPRK clarified its principled stand and attitude towards the denuclearization of the peninsula after the emergence of the nuclear issue between the two countries and advanced a lot of proposals and ways for finding a solution to it. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Even after the appearance of the Bush administration the DPRK manifested the stance that it would regard the U.S. as a friendly nation, not remaining hostile to it, if it stops taking issue with the DPRK's system and imposing sanctions upon it, and has made every effort for finding a peaceful solution to the nuclear issue and improving the bilateral relations. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 There is no change in the DPRK's basic stand to remain committed to the goal of denuclearizing the Korean Peninsula, implement the joint statement adopted at the fourth round of the six-party talks and seek a negotiated peaceful settlement. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The U.S. hard-line conservatives' misinterpretation of the DPRK's stand for the denuclearization of the Peninsula is nothing but a mean trick to mislead the opinion of the nations participating in the six-party talks and the world hoping for the resumption of the talks and shift the responsibility for the talks that remain stalled due to the financial sanctions imposed upon the DPRK by the U.S. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 There can be no smooth and fair talks so long as the U.S. pursues a sinister aim to strangulate the people of the DPRK through sanctions and bring down their system, refusing to co-exist with the latter and trust it. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 If the U.S. truly wants the resumption of the six-party talks and their progress, it had better opt for lifting its financial sanctions against the DPRK and co-existing with it.

Outrages of Ultra-Right Conservatives Criticized in S. Korea
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Pyongyang, January 25 (KCNA) -- The Seoul District Federation of University Student Councils under the south Korean Federation of University Student Councils reportedly made public a statement on Jan. 18 to denounce the ultra-right conservatives for desecrating the grave of Kim Nam Sik, former permanent advisor to Thongil News.
 Ultra-right conservative organizations invited social condemnation for spoiling the graves of unconverted long-term prisoners last year. This time they appeared at the grave of scholar Kim Nam Sik, a champion of reunification, and perpetrated such unethical outrage as painting the gravestone and suspension poster black, the statement said, adding: &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 This vividly proves that the ultra-right conservatives, obsessed by a frenzy of confrontation  in the June 15 era, are leaving no stones unturned to revive the old era. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 We can never pardon the outrages of the anti-reunification forces and the ultra-right conservatives insulting the dead bodies of those who devoted all their life to the patriotic work for reunification and working hard to turn back the June 15 era.

U.S. and S. Korean Warhawks' Moves for War against DPRK Flayed
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Pyongyang, January 25 (KCNA) -- Rodong Sinmun today in a signed commentary denounces the U.S. imperialists and the south Korean warhawks for becoming evermore undisguised in their moves for a war of aggression against the DPRK.
 Some days ago U.S. Secretary of State Rice described the DPRK as a "dangerous regime" and blustered that the U.S. has substantial deterrent against it. U.S. Ambassador in Seoul Bershbow openly made remarks threatening and blackmailing the DPRK. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The warmongers of the south Korean military, at the instigation of their American master, are busy developing and introducing latest war hardware, while talking about "sort of capacity of independently executing a war" and "acquisition of combat power for deterring the north".
 The commentary terms the above-said moves unpardonable criminal acts to throw hurdles in the way of finding a peaceful solution to the nuclear issue between the DPRK and the U.S., escalate confrontation and tensions on the Korean Peninsula and unleash a nuclear war against the DPRK at any cost. 
 The commentary goes on: &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The Bush group uttered that the U.S. is not hostile to north Korea but respects its sovereignty.  But it, in actuality, has made careful preparations in all aspects to mount military attacks on the DPRK anytime. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The outcries let loose by the U.S. trigger-happy circles are little short of declaring that the U.S. has already completed the preparations for a preemptive nuclear attack on the DPRK. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 A war may break out on the Korean Peninsula any moment. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The U.S. imperialists will not escape the fate of the forlorn wandering spirit should they dare ignite a war on this land and invade even an inch of the sky, land and sea of the DPRK. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The south Korean warhawks should bear in mind that their "cooperation" with the U.S. in its moves for a war of aggression against the DPRK, quite contrary to the aspiration of the nation and the trend of the times, would only bring miserable self-destruction.

U.S. Imperialists Threaten Peace in Korean Peninsula, Says Rodong Sinmun
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Pyongyang, January 25 (KCNA) -- The United States is the main force threatening peace as it is creating the danger of a war by continuing aggression and war moves in the Korean Peninsula. 
 Rodong Sinmun today says this in a signed article. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 It goes on: &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The United States has kicked up frantic war rackets against the DPRK from the first day of its occupation of south Korea. Due to the U.S. imperialists' policy of aggression and new war provocation moves, Korea is always under the tense situation in which a war may break out any moment. 
 The presence of the U.S. troops in south Korea clearly proves that the U.S. imperialists are the main force threatening peace in the Korean Peninsula. 
 It is owing to the war provocation moves of the U.S. imperialist aggressor troops stationed in south Korea against peace and reunification that a durable peace has not been achieved in Korea and its peaceful reunification has been delayed. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The U.S. ambition for aggression on the DPRK has become all the more frantic today to stifle it militarily and dominate the whole of Korea. 
 The U.S. is escalating military tension in the Korean Peninsula and bringing about the danger of a nuclear war, while kicking up a nuclear racket against the DPRK and resorting to "sanctions" and "human rights" offensive against it. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 If a war breaks out in the peninsula, the Koreans will suffer irretrievable nuclear disasters. Anybody will fall a victim to it and the existence of the Korean nation itself will be in danger. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 All the Koreans in the north and the south and overseas should turn out as one to foil the U.S. war provocation moves against the DPRK and uproot the source of war from this land through the nation-wide struggle to drive the U.S. troops out of south Korea.

Ten Best Athletes Selected
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Pyongyang, January 25 (KCNA) -- Ten best athletes for Juche 94 (2005) have recently been picked out in the Democratic People's Republic of Korea.
 They are as follow: &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Female judoist Kye Sun Hui of the Moranbong Sports Group who won the world championship at the women's 57 kg category in the 2005 World Judo Championships held in Germany last year; 
 female boxers Ri Hyang Mi of the South Phyongan Provincial Sports Team, Ri Jong Hyang of the Sports Team of the Hamhung Railway Bureau and Yun Kum Ju of the April 25 Sports Group who gave a good account of themselves at the Third Asian Women's Boxing Championships and the Third World Women's Boxing Championships; &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 female judoist An Kum Ae of the Moranbong Sports Group who bagged a gold medal at the 52 kg category in the 2005 Asian Judo Championships; 
 wrestler Cha Kwang Su of the April 25 Sports Group who distinguished himself at the 55 kg category of Greco-roman style wrestling in the 18th Asian Wrestling Championships; &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 female boxer Ri Suk Yong of the Pyongyang City Sports Group who snatched a gold medal at the 66 kg category in the Third Asian Women's Boxing Championships; &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 female pro-boxer Kim Kwang Ok of National Sports School who won the bout for defending the championship of the IFBA at the bantam-weight category and won the bouts for the championship of the WBCF and for defending the title at the bantam-weight category;
 female pro-boxer Ryu Myong Ok of the Sports Team of the Ministry of Commerce who won the bouts for the championship of the IFBA and WBCF at the super-fly-weight category; and  wrestler Jon Hyon Guk of the April 25 Sports Group who gave a good account of himself at the 55 kg category of free style wrestling in the 2005 World Wrestling Championships and the Asian Wrestling Championships.
